network.param.modules.catalogue

Interface ICatalogueManager

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CatalogueManager

    public interface ICatalogueManager
    Perform catalogue related operations ParamNetwork.

    ICatalogueManager add/edit/get/getAll catalogs from the ParamNetwork. Using NetworkManager can able to access this reference.

    ICatalogueManager catalogueManager = networkManager.getCatalogueManager();

    Want to perform any bulk upload items to implement this interface IBulkImport interface for remote files, for local files use FileBulkFileImportConfig.

    ICatalogue defines below categories of operations:

    • addCatalogue method for add java catalogue object into ParamNetwork

    • editCatalogue method for edit java catalogue object into ParamNetwork

    • getCatalogue method for get catalogue object from ParamNetwork

    • getDescription method for getting catalogueIDs from ParamNetwork

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Jitendra Kumar Balla, ParamNetwork

      • addCatalogue

        void addCatalogue(ICatalogue catalogue)
           throws NetworkException,
                  ValidationFailedException
        Method will add catalogue into param network.

        Method will check all the validations checks are pass, system has active internet access and valid key, it will create ICatalogue in the ParamNetwork, Otherwise it will throw an exception.

        Parameters:
        catalogue - Bean Catalogue Object
        Throws:
        NetworkException - Unable to connect to ParamNode it will raise exception.
        ValidationFailedException - Any mandatory files are not set, then this method will throw an ValidationFailedException

        Method will check all the validations checks are pass, system has active internet access and valid key, it will edit ICatalogue in the ParamNetwork, Otherwise it will throw an exception.

      • getCatalogue

        ICatalogue getCatalogue(java.lang.String id)
                 throws AccessDeniedException,
                        NetworkException,
                        RecordNotExistsException
        Method will fetch catalogue into param network.

        First method will check system has active internet access, requested catalogue is exists and Has access for the resource then, it will return ICatalogue. Otherwise it will throw an exception.

        Parameters:
        id - catalogue id
        Throws:
        AccessDeniedException - Not having enough access rights then it will throw an error
        NetworkException - Unable to connect to ParamNode it will raise exception.
        RecordNotExistsException - If record not exists it will throw an error.
